All Classes

Class Description
Account
Abstract class from which Admin and User inherit.
Admin
Class representing the Administrator's account.
Application
Application class containing all the necessary information for its correct use.
Collective
The Collective class represents collectives through which users with similar interests can associate and support different projects all at the same time, being notified when projects are voted and being able to enter and exit this collectives.
District
This class represents the different places where an infrastructural project will be done.
Infrastructural
This class represents the projects of infrastructure type.
Notification
Class used to send messages to users, it simply consists of a title and a text.
Project
This class is the father class of Social and Infrastructural.
ScopeType
This public enumeration defines the scope of a social project.
Social
This class represents the projects of social type.
User
The User class represents the account of a user and all the objects associated with it, including projects, collectives and several attributes such as name, password...
Voter
Interface we used join the things all voters have in common, including functions to count votes, voting and creating projects.
